Class BfaParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jcvi.jillion.maq.bfa.BfaParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FastaParser

    public abstract class BfaParser
extends Object
implements FastaParser
    BfaParser is a FastaParser implementation that can read MAQ's binary fasta file format (.bfa files).

    • Method Detail

      • create

        public static FastaParser create(File bfaFile)
                          throws IOException
        Create a new FastaParser instance to parse the given binary fasta file (bfa) using the system endian. This is the same as calling: create(bfaFile, ByteOrder.nativeOrder())
        Parameters:
        bfaFile - the binary fasta file to parse.
        Returns:
        a new FastaParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the file does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if bfaFile is null.

      • create

        public static FastaParser create(File bfaFile,
                                 ByteOrder endian)
                          throws IOException
        Create a new FastaParser instance to parse the given binary fasta file (bfq) using the given ByteOrder.
        Parameters:
        bfaFile - the binary fasta file to parse.
        endian - the ByteOrder to use to parse the file. Make sure the endian matches the endian of the machine that Maq was run on (or matches the ByteOrder used by the BfaWriterBuilder ) that produced the file.
        Returns:
        a new FastaParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem file does not exist.
        NullPointerException - if either parameter is null.

      • create

        public static FastaParser create(InputStream bfaFileStream)
        Create a new FastaParser instance to parse the given InputStream which contains encoded data in binary fasta file (bfa) format using the system endian. This is the same as calling: create(bfaFileStream, ByteOrder.nativeOrder())
        Parameters:
        bfaFileStream - the InputStream to parse; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new FastaParser instance; will never be null.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if inputstream is null.
